<h3>If-Statement</h3>
<p><b>if</b> is a shell keyword that executes a command (or a set of commands), and checks that command's exit code to see whether it was successful. Depending on that exit code, if executes a specific, different, block of commands.</p>
<div class="codes">
<pre>
    <code>
if [ 1 -gt "$b" ]; then
echo "$b"
fi
    </code>
</pre>
</div>
